cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.MA 

This paper deals with safety verification and control of stochastic hybrid systems, which involves the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. The most relevant sub-category is likely cs.SY (Systems and Control), which deals with the analysis and control of complex systems. The paper also involves probabilistic reasoning and decision making, which suggests the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) may also be relevant. The use of value iteration and Gaussian mixture models suggests the sub-categories cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) may also be relevant.
